ObjectStates.LuaScript:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--                                          Written by Ediforce44                                                     --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- This script contains the main logic for a simple type based deck builder and a more complex version with filters.  --
-- This version of a deck builder should work better than just drawing single cards out of decks and merge them       --
--  together.                                                                                                         --
-- In this script you can configure the deck builder itself, adding filters and set the ratios for the decks.         --
-- Everything that can be configured is marked with a '--conf'. So press (Ctrl + F) and type in: conf                 --
--                                                                                                                    --
-- Before you can use this deck builder you have to load all pre decks into the game.                                 --
--                                                                                                                    --
--                                                                                                                    --
-- If you make use of this script give credits, please.                                                               --                                                                                                                   --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

local SELECTED_BUILD_MODE = nil

BUILD_MODE = {          --conf
    NORMAL      = 1,
    MODE_TWO    = 2,
    MODE_THREE  = 3
    --etc.
}

BUILD_MODE_NAME = {     --conf
    "Normal",
    "All Cards",
    "Only single cards"
}

-- ENTRY_POINT = Object which contains the called function after every deck is build
ENTRY_POINT = {         --conf
    GUID            = "3aaaf4",
    CALL_FUNCTION   = "deckBuilderCallFunction"
}

local function changeBuildMode(newBuildMode)
    -- check if newBuildMode exists
    for _, buildMode in pairs(BUILD_MODE) do
        if buildMode == newBuildMode then
            local newBuildModeName = BUILD_MODE_NAME[newBuildMode] or "Unkown"
            broadcastToAll("New Game Mode selected: " .. newBuildModeName)
            SELECTED_BUILD_MODE = newBuildMode
            return true
        end
    end
    return false
end

function switchBuildMode(params)
    if params.buildMode == nil then
        printToAll("[7E8990][fdd835][WARNING]:[-] Wrong parameter in function switchBuildMode().[-]")
        return false
    end
    return changeBuildMode(params.buildMode)
end

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------      NO GOES       ------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
local ACTIVE_NO_GOES = {}
local nogo_failure_counter = 0

local function isInTable(table, contentToCheck)
    for _, entry in pairs(table) do
        if entry == contentToCheck then
            return true
        end
    end
    return false
end

local function getIntFromScript(luaScript, varName)
    for line in string.gmatch(luaScript,"[^\r\n]+") do
        if string.sub(line,1,#varName) == varName then
            local value = string.match(line,"%d+",#varName)
            return tonumber(value)
        end
    end
    return -1
end

local function customNoGoScriptFunction(luaScript, varName)
    return getIntFromScript(luaScript, varName) > 10
end

NO_GO_TYPES = {         --conf
    NO_GO_ONE_TAG = "NO_GO_ONE_TAG",
    NO_GO_TWO_SCRIPT = "NO_GO_TWO_SCRIPT",
    NO_GO_THREE_NAME = "NO_GO_THREE_NAME"
}

-- objTable needs the following fields:       name,  lua_script,  tags
NO_GO_FILTERS = {       --conf
    NO_GO_ONE_TAG = function(objTable) return isInTable(objTable.tags, "NO_GO_TAG") end,
    NO_GO_TWO_SCRIPT = function(objTable) return customNoGoScriptFunction(objTable.lua_script, "NO_GO_VAR") end,
    NO_GO_THREE_NAME = function(objTable) return false --[[TODO]] end,

    Unkown = function(_)
        nogo_failure_counter = nogo_failure_counter + 1
        return false
    end
}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------      Deck Builder        --------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- RATIO keys <==> PRE_DECK_GUIDS keys
local DECK_ONE_RATIO = {
    {
        TYPE_ONE = 1,
        TYPE_TWO = 1,
        TYPE_THREE = 2,
        TYPE_FOUR = 10,
        TYPE_FIVE = 20,
        TYPE_SIX = 0,
        TYPE_SEVEN = 1,
        TYPE_EIGHT = 55
    },
    {
        TYPE_ONE = 1,
        TYPE_TWO = 2,
        TYPE_THREE = 3,
        TYPE_FOUR = 68,
        TYPE_FIVE = 64,
        TYPE_SIX = 55,
        TYPE_SEVEN = 115,
        TYPE_EIGHT = 117,
        TYPE_NINE = 10      -- Doesn't exist
    },
    {
        TYPE_ONE = 1,
        TYPE_TWO = 1,
        TYPE_THREE = 1,
        TYPE_FOUR = 0,
        TYPE_FIVE = 0,
        TYPE_SIX = 1,
        TYPE_SEVEN = 0,
        TYPE_EIGHT = 1
    }
    --etc.
}

local DECK_INFOS = {        --conf
    DECK_ONE = {
        ID                  = "DECK_ONE",               -- Unique string to access the build deck later
        RATIOS              = DECK_ONE_RATIO,
        NO_GOES             = {},                       -- Optional (If you define it, it will override ACTIVE_NO_GOES for this deck)
        DECK_POSITION       = Vector(-5, 3, -8),
        DECK_ROTATION       = Vector(180, 0, 0),        -- Optional
        DECK_NAME           = "Deck 1",                 -- Optional
        LEFTOVERS_POSITION  = Vector(5, 3, -8),
        LEFTOVERS_ROTATION  = Vector(180, 0, 0),        -- Optional
        LEFTOVERS_NAME      = "Leftovers from Deck 1"   -- Optional
    }
    --etc.
}

local TOTAL_DECK_COUNT = 0  --Will be set in onLoad() function

local function buildDeck(preDeckGUIDs, tagTable)
    local deckAndLeftover = nil
    if #ACTIVE_NO_GOES > 0 then
        deckAndLeftover = buildDeckFilter(preDeckGUIDs, tagTable)       -- If you want to use filter options (see NO GOES)

        if nogo_failure_counter > 0 then
            printToAll("[7E8990][fdd835][WARNING]:[-] Deck Builder: No idea what NO-GO you try to check!? ("
                .. tostring(nogo_failure_counter) .. ")[-]")
        end
    else
        deckAndLeftover = buildDeckSpeed(preDeckGUIDs, tagTable)        -- If you want a fast and smooth deck builder
    end
    return deckAndLeftover
end

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------- Don't change the rest --------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------- Load and Save -------------------------------------------------------
function onLoad(saved_data)

    TOTAL_DECK_COUNT = 0
    for _, _ in pairs(DECK_INFOS) do
        TOTAL_DECK_COUNT = TOTAL_DECK_COUNT + 1
    end

    if saved_data ~= "" then
        local loaded_data = JSON.decode(saved_data)
        if loaded_data[1] ~= nil then
            changeBuildMode(loaded_data[1])
        else
            changeBuildMode(BUILD_MODE.NORMAL)
        end
    end
end

function onSave()
    return JSON.encode({SELECTED_BUILD_MODE})
end

------------------------------------------------------ No goes ---------------------------------------------------------
function setNoGo(params)
    if params.nogo == nil then
        return
    end
    for _, nogo in ipairs(ACTIVE_NO_GOES) do
        if nogo == tostring(params.nogo) then
            return
        end
    end
    table.insert(ACTIVE_NO_GOES, tostring(params.nogo))
end

function setNoGoForDeck(params)
    if params.nogo == nil or params.deckName == nil then
        return
    end
    if DECK_INFOS[params.deckName] == nil then
        return
    end
    local nogoList = DECK_INFOS[params.deckName].NO_GOES or {}
    for _, nogo in ipairs(nogoList) do
        if nogo == tostring(params.nogo) then
            return
        end
    end
    table.insert(nogoList, tostring(params.nogo))
    DECK_INFOS[params.deckName].NO_GOES = nogoList
end

---------------------------------------------------- Deck builder ------------------------------------------------------
local B_waitingDecks = {}

local function deckBuildBarrier(deckType, deck)
    B_waitingDecks[deckType] = deck
    local waitCount = 0
    for _, _ in pairs(B_waitingDecks) do
        waitCount = waitCount + 1
    end
    if waitCount >= TOTAL_DECK_COUNT then
        getObjectFromGUID(ENTRY_POINT.GUID).call(ENTRY_POINT.CALL_FUNCTION, B_waitingDecks)
        B_waitingDecks = {}
    end
end

local function placeDeck(deck, position, rotation, name)
    if deck == nil then
        return
    end
    deck.setPositionSmooth(position, false)
    deck.setRotationSmooth(rotation or Vector(180, 0, 0), false)
    deck.interactable = true
    if name ~= nil then deck.setName(name) end
end

local function setupDeck(buildMode, preDeckGUIDs, deckInfoTable)
    local _temp_currentNoGoes = ACTIVE_NO_GOES
    ACTIVE_NO_GOES = deckInfoTable.NO_GOES or _temp_currentNoGoes
    local createdDecks = buildDeck(preDeckGUIDs, deckInfoTable.RATIOS[buildMode])
    ACTIVE_NO_GOES = _temp_currentNoGoes

    local buildDeck = createdDecks[1]
    local leftoverDeck = createdDecks[2]

    if buildDeck == nil then
        printToAll("[7E8990][fdd835][WARNING]:[-] Can't build deck " .. deckInfoTable.DECK_NAME or "Unkown"
            .. ". [C30000][Please restart this map.][-][-]")
        return
    end

    placeDeck(buildDeck, deckInfoTable.DECK_POSITION, deckInfoTable.DECK_ROTATION, deckInfoTable.DECK_NAME)
    placeDeck(leftoverDeck, deckInfoTable.LEFTOVERS_POSITION, deckInfoTable.LEFTOVERS_ROTATION
        , deckInfoTable.LEFTOVERS_NAME)

    Wait.condition(function() deckBuildBarrier(deckInfoTable.ID, buildDeck) end, function() return buildDeck.resting end)
end

function buildAllDecks(params)
    local buildMode = SELECTED_BUILD_MODE
    if params.preDecks == nil then
        printToAll("[7E8990][fdd835][WARNING]:[-] Wrong parameters in Deck Builder function 'buildAllDecks()'.[-]")
    end
    for deckName, infoTable in pairs(DECK_INFOS) do
        setupDeck(buildMode, params.preDecks[deckName], infoTable)
    end
end

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------- Implementation of the two deck builder ------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
local function mergeCards(cards)
    local buildDeck = cards[1]
    if #cards > 1 then
        buildDeck = buildDeck.putObject(cards[2])
        for i = 3, #cards do
            buildDeck.putObject(cards[i])
            destroyObject(cards[i])                 -- Necessary for TTS (otherwise TTS would create card duplicates)
        end
    end
    return buildDeck
end

local function mergeDecks(decks, startDeck)
    local buildDeck = nil
    if (startDeck ~= nil) and (startDeck.type == "Deck") then
        buildDeck = startDeck
        for _, nextDeck in pairs(decks) do
            if nextDeck ~= nil then
                buildDeck.putObject(nextDeck)
                destroyObject(nextDeck)             -- Necessary for TTS (otherwise TTS would create card duplicates)
            end
        end
    else
        for index, nextDeck in pairs(decks) do
            if nextDeck.type == "Deck" then
                table.remove(decks, index)
                return mergeDecks(decks, nextDeck)
            end
        end

        if #decks > 0 then
            buildDeck = mergeCards(decks)
        end
    end

    return buildDeck
end

local function checkForNoGoes(objTable)
    for _, noGoType in pairs(ACTIVE_NO_GOES) do
        if (NO_GO_FILTERS[noGoType] or NO_GO_FILTERS.Unkown)(objTable) then
            return false
        end
    end
    return true
end

local function takeCardsFromDeck(deck, cardGUIDs, takenCardsTable)
    for _, guid in pairs(cardGUIDs) do
        table.insert(takenCardsTable, deck.takeObject({guid = guid}))
    end
    return takenCardsTable
end

function buildDeckSpeed(preDeckGUIDs, tagTable)
    local selectedDecks = {}
    local leftoverDecks = {}
    for type, amountToTake in pairs(tagTable) do
        if preDeckGUIDs[type] ~= nil then
            local preDeck = getObjectFromGUID(preDeckGUIDs[type])
            if amountToTake > 0 then
                if preDeck.tag == "Deck" then
                    -- For the edge case that only one card should be choosen
                    if amountToTake == 1 then
                        if preDeck.getQuantity() == 2 then
                            local secondCardGUID = preDeck.getObjects()[2].guid
                            table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck.takeObject())
                            table.insert(leftoverDecks, getObjectFromGUID(secondCardGUID))
                        else
                            table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck.takeObject())
                            table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
                        end
                    elseif amountToTake == (preDeck.getQuantity() - 1) then
                        local cardLeft = preDeck.takeObject()
                        table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                        table.insert(leftoverDecks, cardLeft)
                    else
                        local splitDecks = preDeck.cut(preDeck.getQuantity() - amountToTake)
                        if splitDecks ~= nil then
                            table.insert(leftoverDecks, splitDecks[2])
                        end
                        table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                    end
                else
                    table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                end
            else
                table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
            end
        end
    end

    return {mergeDecks(selectedDecks), mergeDecks(leftoverDecks)}
end

local function _dbf_takeFirstAcceptableCard(preDeck)
    local selectedCard = nil
    local leftoverDeck = preDeck
    if preDeck.getQuantity() == 2 then
        local preDeckObjects = preDeck.getObjects()
        if checkForNoGoes(preDeckObjects[1]) then
            selectedCard = preDeck.takeObject({guid = preDeckObjects[1].guid})
            leftoverDeck = getObjectFromGUID(preDeckObjects[2].guid)
        elseif checkForNoGoes(preDeckObjects[2]) then
            selectedCard = preDeck.takeObject({guid = preDeckObjects[2].guid})
            leftoverDeck = getObjectFromGUID(preDeckObjects[1].guid)
        end
    else
        for _, objTable in pairs(preDeck.getObjects())do
            if checkForNoGoes(objTable) then
                selectedCard = preDeck.takeObject({guid = objTable.guid})
                break
            end
        end
    end
    return {selectedCard, leftoverDeck}
end

local function _dbf_determineGoodAndBadCards(preDeck, amountToTake)
    local cardsToRemove = {}
    local cardsToKeep = {}
    local goodCards = 0
    for _, objTable in pairs(preDeck.getObjects()) do
        if checkForNoGoes(objTable) then
            table.insert(cardsToKeep, objTable.guid)
            goodCards = goodCards + 1
            if goodCards == amountToTake then
                break
            end
        else
            table.insert(cardsToRemove, objTable.guid)
        end
    end
    return {GOOD = cardsToKeep, BAD = cardsToRemove, GOOD_AMOUNT = #cardsToKeep, BAD_AMOUNT = #cardsToRemove}
end

function buildDeckFilter(preDeckGUIDs, tagTable)
    local selectedDecks = {}
    local leftoverDecks = {}
    for type, amountToTake in pairs(tagTable) do
        if preDeckGUIDs[type] ~= nil then
            local preDeck = getObjectFromGUID(preDeckGUIDs[type])
            if amountToTake > 0 then
                if preDeck.tag == "Deck" then
                    -- For the edge case that only one card should be choosen
                    if amountToTake == 1 then
                        local selectionTable = _dbf_takeFirstAcceptableCard(preDeck)
                        if selectionTable[1] ~= nil then
                            table.insert(selectedDecks, selectionTable[1])
                        end
                        table.insert(leftoverDecks, selectionTable[2])
                    else
                        local goodAndBad = _dbf_determineGoodAndBadCards(preDeck, amountToTake)
                        if goodAndBad.GOOD_AMOUNT > 0 then
                            if goodAndBad.GOOD_AMOUNT > goodAndBad.BAD_AMOUNT then
                                -- More good than bad cards
                                leftoverDecks = takeCardsFromDeck(preDeck, goodAndBad.BAD, leftoverDecks)
                                if (goodAndBad.GOOD_AMOUNT + goodAndBad.BAD_AMOUNT) < preDeck.getQuantity() then
                                    -- There are more cards in the preDeck than the counted good and bad cards
                                        -- This appears if _dbf_determineGoodAndBadCards() found enough good cards to return
                                    if goodAndBad.GOOD_AMOUNT == (preDeck.getQuantity() - 1) then
                                        -- One needless card left
                                        local cardLeft = preDeck.takeObject({top = false})
                                        table.insert(leftoverDecks, cardLeft)
                                        table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                                    else
                                        -- More than one needless card left => cut()
                                        local splitDecks = preDeck.cut(goodAndBad.GOOD_AMOUNT)
                                        if splitDecks ~= nil then
                                            table.insert(selectedDecks, splitDecks[2])
                                        end
                                        table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
                                    end
                                else
                                    -- Whole deck is split into good and bad cards
                                    table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                                end
                            else
                                -- More bad than good cards
                                selectedDecks = takeCardsFromDeck(preDeck, goodAndBad.GOOD, selectedDecks)
                                table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
                            end
                        else
                            -- No good cards found
                            table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
                        end
                    end
                else
                    -- preDeck is Card
                    if checkForNoGoes({name = preDeck.getName(), lua_script = preDeck.getLuaScript()
                        , tags = preDeck.getTags()}) then
                        table.insert(selectedDecks, preDeck)
                    else
                        table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
                    end
                end
            else
                -- No cards needed from this preDeck
                table.insert(leftoverDecks, preDeck)
            end
        end
    end

    return {mergeDecks(selectedDecks), mergeDecks(leftoverDecks)}
end

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--                                          Written by Ediforce44                                                     --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- This should be your own setup script. This script is only a dummy. Your setup script should shuffle the pre decks  --
--  and call the buildAllDecks() function from the deck builder, like the first function in this script.              --
-- You can also add pre deck guids dynamically before you call the deck builder. But be aware that they have to match --
--  the ratio keys from the deck builder configuration in order to work. Otherwise they will be ignored.              --
--                                                                                                                    --
-- After the deck builder is done with building the decks, it will call your configured function (in this case it is  --
--  deckBuilderCallFunction()). You can configure the called function inside of the deck builder script.              --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PRE_DECK_HANDLER_GUID   = "ed1b96"      -- Object which contains the Pre-Deck logic
DECK_BUILDER_GUID       = "66cd21"

function callDeckBuilder(gameLanguage)
    local preDeckHandler = getObjectFromGUID(PRE_DECK_HANDLER_GUID)
    local preDeckGUIDs = preDeckHandler.call("getPreDeckGUIDs", {language = gameLanguage})
    preDeckHandler.call("shufflePreDecks", {preDecks = preDeckGUIDs})

    --TODO: On this point you can add further Pre-Deck GUIDs to make it more dynamic
        -- Keep in mind you have to match the Deck Ratio Keys from the deck builder
            -- (so add the types to the Deck Ratio if you insert new type Pre-Decks)

    Wait.frames(
        function()
            getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID).call("buildAllDecks", {preDecks = preDeckGUIDs})
        end)
end

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------     Called after decks are build     ------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
function deckBuilderCallFunction(deckTable)
    log(deckTable)
    --TODO: Do what ever you want with the built decks
        -- Remember: Keys from deckTable are the deck IDs which you set in the DECK_INFOS table
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--                                          Written by Ediforce44                                                     --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- This script contains the logic for a handling the pre decks for this deck builder.                                 --                                                                                                        --
-- In this script you can configure the pre deck settings, adding types of pre decks and set their guids.             --
-- Everything that can be configured is marked with a '--conf'. So press (Ctrl + F) and type in: conf                 --
--                                                                                                                    --
-- Before you can use this deck builder you have to load all pre decks into the game.                                 --
-- Pre-Decks are decks/single cards which are used to build a final deck. Every pre decks should consist of cards     --
--  from one type. You can configure the ratios of the types for the final deck in the deck builder script.           --
--                                                                                                                    --
--                                                                                                                    --
-- If you make use of this script give credits, please.                                                               --                                                                                                                   --
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- RATIO keys <==> PRE_DECK_GUIDS keys
PRE_DECK_GUIDS = {                      --conf
    US = {
        DECK_ONE = {
            TYPE_ONE = "d1d9c4",
            TYPE_TWO = "c4e92a",
            TYPE_THREE = "b586d7",
            TYPE_FOUR = "97f2f5",
            TYPE_FIVE = "4b5a23",
            TYPE_SIX = "b5c9be",
            TYPE_SEVEN = "3080e9",
            TYPE_EIGHT = "899c9e"
        }
        --DECK_TWO = {
            --etc.
        --}
    }
    --etc.
}

function shufflePreDecks(params)
    local preDecks = nil

    if params.language == nil then
        if params.preDecks == nil then
            printToAll("[7E8990][fdd835][WARNING]:[-] Wrong parameters in Table Base function 'shufflePreDecks()'.[-]")
            return
        else
            preDecks = params.preDecks
        end
    else
        preDecks = PRE_DECK_GUIDS[params.language]
    end

    for _, preDeck in pairs(preDecks) do
        for _, guid in pairs(preDeck) do
            local obj = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
            if obj.tag == "Deck" then
                obj.shuffle()
            end
        end
    end
end

function getPreDeckGUIDs(params)
    local language = params.language
    if language == nil then
        language = "US"
    end
    return PRE_DECK_GUIDS[language]
end

local DECK_BUILDER_GUID = "66cd21"
local SETUP_SCRIPT_GUID = "3aaaf4"

local function createButtons()
    self.createButton({
        click_function = "dbModeOne",
        label = "DB Mode 1",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {-5, 0, 1.5},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 2000,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })

    self.createButton({
        click_function = "dbModeTwo",
        label = "DB Mode 2",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {0, 0, 1.5},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 2000,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })

    self.createButton({
        click_function = "dbModeThree",
        label = "DB Mode 3",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {5, 0, 1.5},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 2000,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })

    self.createButton({
        click_function = "onStart",
        label = "Start Deckbuilder",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {0, 0, 4},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 3200,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })
end

function onLoad()
    createButtons()
end

function dbModeOne()
    local deckBuilder = getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID)
    deckBuilder.call("switchBuildMode", {buildMode = deckBuilder.getTable("BUILD_MODE").NORMAL})
end

function dbModeTwo()
    local deckBuilder = getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID)
    deckBuilder.call("switchBuildMode", {buildMode = deckBuilder.getTable("BUILD_MODE").MODE_TWO})
end

function dbModeThree()
    local deckBuilder = getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID)
    deckBuilder.call("switchBuildMode", {buildMode = deckBuilder.getTable("BUILD_MODE").MODE_THREE})
end

function onStart()
    getObjectFromGUID(SETUP_SCRIPT_GUID).call("callDeckBuilder")
end

local DECK_BUILDER_GUID = "66cd21"

local function createButtons()
    self.createButton({
        click_function = "nogoTag",
        label = "NOGO Tag",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {4, 0, -1},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 2500,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })

    self.createButton({
        click_function = "nogoScript",
        label = "NOGO Script",
        function_owner = self,
        position = {4, 0, 1},
        rotation = {0, 0, 0},
        color = {1, 1, 1},
        width = 2500,
        height = 500,
        font_size = 400
    })
end

function onLoad()
    createButtons()
end

function nogoTag()
    local deckBuilder = getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID)
    deckBuilder.call("setNoGoForDeck", {nogo = deckBuilder.getTable("NO_GO_TYPES").NO_GO_ONE_TAG, deckName = "DECK_ONE"})
    broadcastToAll("NOGO activated: " .. deckBuilder.getTable("NO_GO_TYPES").NO_GO_ONE_TAG)
end

function nogoScript()
    local deckBuilder = getObjectFromGUID(DECK_BUILDER_GUID)
    deckBuilder.call("setNoGoForDeck"
        , {nogo = deckBuilder.getTable("NO_GO_TYPES").NO_GO_TWO_SCRIPT, deckName = "DECK_ONE"})
    broadcastToAll("NOGO activated: " .. deckBuilder.getTable("NO_GO_TYPES").NO_GO_TWO_SCRIPT)
end
